      "content": "but i checked all that. my fridge is off, the plumbing is fine, and there is zero construction nearby. the thing is, i can literally feel them doing it when they get home. it's not like a machine running, it's like a rhythmic pulse that just... hits me. and every time it happens, i feel this sudden wave of irritation. it feels way too intentional to be a broken pipe or something. don't you think it's possible they're using some kind of low-freq tech to mess with people's heads?",
